d [b]10 or more times[/b].[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Upon reaching [b]Lv. 50[/b], a character is immediately considered a [b]Dungeon Helper[/b] for all [b]Normal Adventure Dungeons Lv. 49 and below[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list][*]A [b]Dungeon Rookie[/b] is a player who has successfully cleared a dungeon [b]9 or fewer times[/b].[/*]\r\n[*]The amount of coins gained remains constant, regardless of the number of rookies in the party. Extra rookies in the party does not mean extra coins. But it does mean you are helping more people! Thank you![/*]\r\n[*]All dungeons located under the [b]Main[/b] tab in the [b]Challenge Map[/b] are eligible to have Dungeon Helper guidance.[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]This includes Normal/Hard Adventure Dungeons, Chaos Raids, and Eye of Lapenta raids.[/*]\r\n[/list][*]You can obtain a maximum [b]of 10 Dungeon Helper Coins each day[/b]. The limit resets at midnight server time.[/*]\r\n[*][b]You will still receive Dungeon Helper Coins[/b] even if you have reached your Daily or Weekly Dungeon Cap[/*]\r\n[*]You can spend your Dungeon Helper Coins at [b]Spartan's Shop[/b] in [b]Queenstown[/b].[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Besides furniture, all purchasable items are [b]character-bound[/b].[/*]\r\n[*]Epic Armor Bonus Value Re-roller, Legendary Armor Bonus Value Re-roller, Epic Armor Attribute Lock Scroll, Epic Accessory Attribute Lock Scroll, Legendary Accessory Attribute Lock Scroll, Legendary Armor Attribute Lock Scroll [b]expire at the last day of month following the current month[/b] (ex: if purchased on July 25th, the item will expire at the end of August).[/*]\r\n[/list][/list][*][b]Dungeon Helper Coin Rewards[/b]:[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]7 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Elixir[/b] (up to 5 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]5 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Legendary Armor Bonus Value Re-roller[/b] (up to 2 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]5 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Legendary Armor Attribute Lock Scroll[/b] (up to 2 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]5 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Accessory Attribute Lock Scroll (Legendary)[/b] (up to 2 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]3 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Epic Armor Bonus Value Re-roller[/b] (up to 4 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]3 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Epic Armor Attribute Lock Scroll[/b] (up to 4 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]3 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Accessory Attribute Lock Scroll (Epic)[/b] (up to 2 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]2 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]100 Crystal Fragments[/b] (up to 5 per week)[/*]\r\n[*]300 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Tamed Little Horus Epic Ground Mount[/b][/*]\r\n[*]300 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Winged War Horse Epic Ground Mount[/b][/*]\r\n[*]200 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Little Horus Non-Combat Pet[/b][/*]\r\n[*]200 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Proud Sphinx Cat Non-Combat Pet[/b][/*]\r\n[*]100 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Silver Vagabond Bamboo Hat Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]100 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Magic Stone Hat Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]90 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Silver Vagabond Vest Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]90 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Silver Vagabond Pants Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]90 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Magic Stone Top Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]90 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Magic Stone Bottoms Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]60 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Silver Vagabond Gloves Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]60 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Silver Vagabond Boots Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]60 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Magic Stone Gloves Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]60 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Magic Stone Shoes Outfit[/b][/*]\r\n[*]30 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Dungeon Helper Name Tag (30 Day)[/b][/*]\r\n[*]20 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]World Chat Voucher[/b][/*]\r\n[*]20 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Rooftop Dragon Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]13 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Happy Princess Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]13 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Small Dragon Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]13 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Baby Dragon Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]12 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Auto-Fishing Voucher (1 Hour)[/b][/*]\r\n[*]9 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Pollen Fanfare Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]6 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Entrance Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]5 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Free Rotors Walkie-talkie[/b][/*]\r\n[*]5 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Shield Decoration Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[*]3 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Channel Chat Voucher[/b][/*]\r\n[*]3 Dungeon Helper Coins: [b]Knight's Tower: Stairs Furnishing[/b][/*]\r\n[/list][/list]\r\n[h1]Job Rank II Skill Rebalance[/h1]\r\n\r\nIn an ongoing effort to improve the game experience for all players, regardless of what selections they make in class or build, we improved skills for different classes that we felt were lacking.\r\n\r\nThese adjustments may not be the final changes we make to classes, so please continue providing feedback. We are especially interested in hearing from players who try out some of the lesser-used skill branches after these adjustments are made.\r\n\r\nPlease bear in mind that not all suggestions made by players could be accommodated, as some of them run the risk of creating greater balance problems in the future. We tried to use your feedback as much as possible when planning out these changes, and will keep them in mind when we examine class balance again in the future.\r\n\r\n[b]Archer[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Archer players suffered from dealing a little less damage than the other DPS who were bringing buffs to the table. Moreover, their Wind Focus, despite potentially being more powerful than their Fire Focus, felt very clunky to play due to animation locks. We boosted their damage a little bit so that they can even the playing field when facing down a single target, and improved the main attraction of the Wind Focus while also making Greater Sharp Eyes a more useful tool.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Flame Arrow's[/b] damage has been increased across the board ([b]8%[/b], [b]15%[/b], and [b]16%[/b] respectively per stage), and the damage of the three-arrow combo has been made constant, instead of being heavily front-loaded. Additionally, [b]Flame Arrow IV's[/b] damage was increased by [b]22%[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/cc4f880ed0d22536262b2236d42d785c5232c03b.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Damage from each [b]Multi-Drive Shot[/b] arrow has been increased by[b] 30%[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/7babf163bcfb56c4af40a8205f85315e2c6796ff.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Greater Sharp Eyes[/b] further increases the amount of damage dealt by the Archer, and the [b]buff's duration has been increased to 40 seconds[/b] (up from 30 seconds).[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/b67eb7b310e3addf9db159af2c0b9ccd87533cb0.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Twirling Wind Arrow's[/b] channel animation was [b]reduced by 40%[/b]. Please note that, despite rumors to the contrary, this skill is also affected by Attack Speed.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]Assassin[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Give me more Spirit! Assassin players have been suffering from issues of SP starvation for a very long time, which often led to a lot of memes about them. Needless to say, many of you commented that when the class works, it feels right. So, in an attempt to address the issue, we made a few cost adjustments. While these don't fully address the SP issue at its core, it should hopefully greatly alleviate the burden. Adjusting Redoubled Pain to be able to critical hit on it's main damage source will require careful monitoring to make sure it's not too powerful.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Redoubled Pain's[/b] SP cost has been reduced to [b]9 SP[/b] (from 11 SP).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Redoubled Pain[/b] can now score a [b]critical hit when consuming the poison[/b].[/*]\r\n[*][b]Binding Punishment's[/b] SP cost has been [b]reduced to 15 SP[/b] (from 20 SP).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Dark Mire's[/b] SP cost has been [b]reduced to 30 SP[/b] (from 40 SP).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Assassin's Circle[/b] can now score a [b]critical hit[/b].[/*]\r\n[*][b]Shadow Stance[/b] has gained [b]additional Dark Damage[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/f1f25c9ca70f43c7bed9de1558f6ba95a681c6a3.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]Berserker[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]The Berserker's Bleed Focus is notoriously powerful for dealing super-fast damage, while being nearly indestructible thanks to the Raging Soul buff. We elected not to touch this skill tree at all and instead focus on the Swordplay Focus of Berserker, designed around slow but impactful hits. By slightly adjusting the cooldown of Aerial Smash it should seamlessly flow out of two cycles of Skull Splitter. Additionally, we're increasing the amount of power Blood Fury provides while also increasing its trigger threshold from 30% all the way up to 50%. That'll really let this focus excel in the second half of battles, rather than the last leg of the fight with dynamic Skull Splitter resets, Dark Aura resets, and powerful Bloodlust mini-nukes.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The [b]physical attack bonus[/b] provided by [b]Blood Fury[/b] has been increased.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/cb0d61e3c00259546aefa100ffcf35bd0122f235.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Aerial Smash's[/b] cooldown has been reduced to [b]7 seconds[/b] (down from 8 seconds).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Blood Fury[/b] will now activate when striking a target [b]below 50% max HP[/b] (up from 30%).[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]Heavy Gunner[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Heavy Gunner has been in a solid spot in terms of ranged DPS, but the Plasma Focus was lacking due to a number of inhibiting problems that made it finicky to use. Some slight adjustments should make it more enjoyable to play while also centering the spotlight on the Plasma Focus' Sky Hunter, which may require additional attention later to make it less difficult to use. As Heavy Gunner is a DPS class with no utility, we will closely monitor to see if it needs additional improvements to get it where it should be compared to other classes.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Plasma Chain's[/b] explosion can now score a [b]critical hit[/b].[/*]\r\n[*][b]Sky Hunter's[/b] cooldown was reduced to [b]30 seconds[/b] (down from 60 seconds).[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]Knight[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]When it came to the Knight, we felt like the class was already in a good place with damage in the Longsword Focus. However, halfway down the Shield Focus of the Job Rank II skills we felt like its ultimate skill, Heaven's Judgment, was far too weak. We've made some slight adjustments to damage and will come back to this skill branch later to see what else we can do to make it as appealing as the Sword Focus, but centered on support. This is just a start.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The skill damage of [b]Heaven's Judgment[/b] has been increased by [b]10%[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/8112c54aaca9ab354c7cf889bd54d906e896893f.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]Priest[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Priest characters ran into an issue where if they weren't providing much-needed healing in content where it was needed, they were often passed over in favor of a more powerful damage-dealing class or a Soul Binder. In order to make them more appealing, we've made slight adjustments to make their support a little better and more consistent, while also improving their Battle Focus so that multiple Priests can play together with far fewer drawbacks than how it is currently.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The damage amplification provided by [b]Vitality[/b] has been increased.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/77b4f3477bc07f3858f1fb4fc9fb68951d663512.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Divine Wave's[/b] chance to activate additional damage as well as heal has been [b]increased to 25%[/b] (from 12%).[/*]\r\n[*]The bonus damage of [b]Light Sword[/b] can now score a [b]critical hit[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]Runeblade[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]For Runeblade characters, its Rune Focus, the lesser known little brother of the Blade Focus, is often neglected. We've made some minor adjustments to its damage so that players interested in the Rune Focus can do so; however the bulk of the Rune Focus' power will come in a later update.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Rune Trigger's[/b] damage has been increased by [b]15%[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/2d541151d3e8cbd51e391c89b593c7998432a9b0.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Dimension Blade's[/b] damage has been increased by [b]20%[/b] and the SP cost has been [b]reduced to 20 SP[/b] (down from 30 SP).[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/0473dcc4577ce25113a3ee706a28fffe0ebfe189.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Under the [b]Fire Sigil[/b], [b]Quintuple Cut[/b] is now able to score [b]critical hits[/b] from its bonus damage.[/*]\r\n[*]Under the [b]Lightning Sigil[/b], [b]Dimension Blade[/b] is now able to score [b]critical hits[/b] from its bonus damage.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]Striker[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]No changes were needed to Striker, whose skill focuses are good as they are currently.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Nothing![/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]Soul Binder[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Vision is an all-powerful omnipotent being… but compared to the powerful Animus Focus, it's currently hard to justify playing with Vision. We've increased the damage accordingly so that it can at least be a proper contender. Soul Binder will also receive the only nerf for this update, a decrease to the potency of Soul Cube, while also gaining the option for the shield to be similarly powerful by expending one of their Awakened Mantra. This skill was far too overpowered in its current state and made other classes' survivability issues obsolete. It will still retain its title of the strongest shield, just now the Soul Binder will have to sacrifice some damage in order for the shield to be as powerful as it was before.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Vision Torrent's magic attack bonus[/b] has been increased.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/0bfe9e43c8cab66cafeb914d63f26e47bc6e5bcd.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Vision Torrent's[/b] duration has been [b]increased to 25 seconds[/b] (up from 20 seconds).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Spirit Bound[/b] sees an increase in damage by [b]15%[/b] when [b]enhanced[/b] hitting a single target.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/bc7ae00f3aa9969215bd654b11ac67d0403e541b.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Vision Crush's[/b] SP cost has been [b]reduced to 25 SP[/b] (down from 40 SP).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Soul Cube's[/b] HP overshield has been [b]reduced across the board[/b]. Empowering it with an Awakened Mantra Orb will increase the potency of the shield.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/b5af78958da898598f5e47cc1f369b9fcb5bcd1b.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]Thief[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Thief is already a top contender when it comes to dishing out damage. We wanted to focus more on bringing on some overall quality of life improvements to the class that'll make both building and playing it more comfortable. The Poison Focus saw a small buff to put it up to pace with its stronger Shadow Focus.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Battle Step[/b] has been changed into an [b]active skill[/b] rather than a passive skill.[/*]\r\n[*]The [b]Retaliation[/b] buff will now last [b]18 seconds[/b] (up from 12 seconds).[/*]\r\n[*]Players will only require [b]Lv. 3 Mind Breaker[/b] to proceed to leveling [b]Haste[/b] (down from Lv. 5).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Shadow Step's[/b] cooldown has been reduced to [b]6 seconds[/b] (from 7 seconds) and the engage distance has been increased to [b]12m[/b] (from 8m).[/*]\r\n[*][b]Shadow Step[/b] will now grant [b]Rush[/b] for [b]8 seconds[/b] when cast.[/*]\r\n[*][b]Poison Master[/b] now grants additional [b]Poison Damage[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/411485165787a895827822e8f991df1ea753f6f5.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]Wizard[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]The Storm Focus of the Wizard was lacking a great deal of firepower that the Fire Focus had, even though both skill trees had a great deal of complexity. By increasing the raw output of the Storm Focus, we hope that it could see situationally similar use to the Fire Focus with a different but still-exciting playstyle. We would still like to revisit the subject of the frustrations Fire Wizards have to deal with, so we ask that you give us additional time to resolve some of the playstyle problems.[/i]\r\n[list]\r\n[*][b]Dual Cast's[/b] skill damage has been increased: [b]15%[/b] for [b]Handy Lightning[/b] and [b]20%[/b] for [b]Ice Shot[/b], and the [b]SP cost[/b] has been [b]reduced to 13[/b] (down from 15 SP).[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/19f5dd4d95168ddfa796fb9b43a57b360e309455.png[/img]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]When [b]Ice Cream Time[/b] and [b]Thunderbolt[/b] are on the same Macro Key, the game will always try to [b]prioritize Ice Cream Time[/b] first.[/*]\r\n[*][b]Perfect Storm's damage[/b] has been increased by [b]15%[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/49d8aaf8e374884827f15e5929a8894f0f86bbd9.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[h1]Hard Adventure Dungeon Rebalance &amp; Trader's Ribbons[/h1]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]We've been going over the current state of new players and the trials they have to go through from the moment they start their adventures in Lith Harbor all the way through their progression to the latest challenges.[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]After reading a great deal of feedback and going over the content from our side, we've decided that in order to make the ease into higher level dungeons more gradual, we will decrease the stats of the enemies you encounter.[/*]\r\n[*]The [b]HP of all enemies[/b] (including bosses) will be [b]reduced by 25%[/b] in the following dungeons:[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The Song of the Oracle[/*]\r\n[*]Guardian of the Seas[/*]\r\n[*]Icethorn Ridge[/*]\r\n[*]Malevolent Manor[/*]\r\n[*]Madrakan Ramparts[/*]\r\n[*]Madrakan's Heart[/*]\r\n[/list][*]The [b]damage of all enemies[/b] (including bosses) will be [b]reduced by 30%[/b] in the following dungeons:[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The Song of the Oracle[/*]\r\n[*]Guardian of the Seas[/*]\r\n[/list][*]We hope that by making the enemies easier to defeat that newer players challenging the content will be able to more easily push through adversaries while more experienced players can enjoy more visceral combat with the slew of enemies.[/*]\r\n[/list][*]A total of 98 Lv. 60 Trader's Ribbons can be earned a week from A-rank rewards in Lv. 60 Chaos Raids and Eye of Lapenta Dungeons.[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Trader's Ribbons can be used on Lv. 60 [b]Epic[/b] or [b]Legendary[/b] equipment that hasn't yet been equipped on a character.[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Double-clicking on the ribbons in your inventory will open a UI which will allow you to place an item in the window to unbind it.[/*]\r\n[*]The amount of ribbons required varies depending on the equipment type. The amount of ribbons needed is listed in the item's tooltip.[/*]\r\n[*]Unbound items can be [b]traded once[/b] or [b]sold on the Black Market[/b], but [b]cannot be moved between characters on the account[/b].[/*]\r\n[/list][*]Trader's Ribbons are rewarded once per week for achieving [b]A-rank[/b] in the following Chaos Raids and Eye of Lapenta Dungeons:[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Frostpillar Temple (Hard): 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[*]Madrakan Spire (Hard): 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[*]Rock ‘n' Rollin' Pink Bean (Hard): 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[*]Emerald Prison: 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[*]Azure Flux: 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[*]Terminus of Time: 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[*]Blackshard Nexus: 14 Ribbons[/*]\r\n[/list][/list][/list]\r\n[h1]Maple Life Updates[/h1]\r\n\r\n[b]Meso House Assistants[/b]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The benefits of a house assistant are no longer limited by spending Merets![/*]\r\n[*]Meso house assistants can create all the same things Meret house assistants can.[/*]\r\n[*]Meret house assistants are still useful though, so fret not! Besides looking great, they require fewer materials to craft what you request of them![/*]\r\n[*]You can purchase housing assistance with mesos in \"My Home -> Build Mode\".[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[img]https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steamcommunity/public/images/clans/33702547/2955058fb62669e0e534456a431f2ea5184dc5ab.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]Overworld House Plot Discount[/b]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]All overworld house plots' purchase, rent, and contract extension costs will be [b]permanently reduced by 90%[/b]![/*]\r\n[*]This is effective in all house plot locations and sizes indefinitely.[/*]\r\n[/list]\r\n[b]New Housing Blocks[/b]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]You asked for them! Eighteen Arcade-themed blocks will be permanently added to the list of available housing blocks in \"My Home -> Build Mode\". These blocks are free-of-cost to help you explore your creative side when building.[/*]\r\n[*]Blocks include:[/*]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Glass Divider[/*]\r\n[*]Glass Divider Corner[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Camera Booth[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Claw Game[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Dancing Game[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Foosball Table[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Pool Table[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Toy Display[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Toy Machine[/*]\r\n[*]Joyful Toy Showcase[/*]\r\n[*]Maple Toy Stand[/*]\r\n[*]Red Maple Toy Box[/*]\r\n[*]Two different Metal Blocks[/*]\r\n[*]Three different Picture Frames[/*]\r\n[*]Yellow Maple Toy Box[/*]\r\n[/list][/list]\r\n[h1]Miscellaneous Updates[/h1]\r\n[list]\r\n[*]The \"Outfits\" inventory tab can be expanded up to 210 slots (up from 150).[/*]\r\n[*]The \"Pets\" inventory tab can be expanded up to 138 slots (up from 60).[/*]\r\n[*]The image for in-game announcements has been changed to Vanilla 